Carbohydrate EAR and RDA Summary, Ages 19 Years and Older

EAR for Women and Men
>= 19 years
100 g/d of carbohydrate

The RDA for carbohydrate is set by using a CV (coefficient of variation) of 15 percent based on the
variation in brain glucose utilization.(sauce????)

The RDA is defined as equal to the
EAR plus twice the CV to cover the needs of 97 to 98 percent of the
individuals in the group
BB: RDA = EAR + 2 (0.1 × EAR) = 1.2 × EAR. (this is at the "Introduction to DRI" section of this document)


(therefore, for carbohydrate the RDA is 130 per-
cent of the EAR).

